de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.core
Class Sense

java.lang.Object
  de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.abstracts.HasMonolingualExternalRefs
      de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.core.Sense
All Implemented Interfaces:
IHasDefinitions, IHasFrequencies, IHasID, IHasMonolingualExternalRefs, IHasSemanticLabels, java.lang.Comparable<Sense>
public class Sense
extends HasMonolingualExternalRefs
implements IHasID, IHasDefinitions, IHasFrequencies, IHasSemanticLabels, java.lang.Comparable<Sense>

Sense is a class representing one meaning of a lexical entry.
The Sense class allows for hierarchical senses in that a sense may be more specific than another sense of the same lexical entry.

Author:
Zijad Maksuti
See Also:
LexicalEntry

setTransparentMeaning

public void setTransparentMeaning(boolean flag)
Sets the transparent meaning flag to this Sense instance.

Explanation:
If the syntactic head of a phrase is not its semantic center, it has a transparent meaning, i.e. it merely adds information to the semantic center of the phrase.

Parameters:
flag - set it to true to indicate that the sense has a transparent meaning, or to false otherwise

isTransparentMeaning

public boolean isTransparentMeaning()

Returns:
true if the sense has a transparent meaning, false otherwise
